healthy forgiveness is true forgiveness written in a compassionate and wise manner intended for those who have experienced a very harrowing situation , this book explores and offers emotionally healthy tools for healing the deepest hurts inflicted by someone very close to us . based on real-life case stories the book explores in a reality-oriented manner the paradox of true forgiveness that allows deep and complete healing for a person . this is not about blaming the victim or sugar-coated attempts at glossing over mud with whip cream ... it is getting to the core hurt and really mending a broken heart so it is stronger and wiser and safer than before . a must read